[31]The Sayner Hütte in Bendorf am Rhein, which was specialized in the processes of metal smelting of ancient models, in 1829, he made a copy of the long 19-inch Column on the project of the artist Heinrich Zumpft according to the drawings of Carl Osterwald.
[32]One of the first castings in bronze came in may of 1829 to Goethe in Weimar.
